===Etymology===
Ancient forms: [[斆]], [[斅]]. The former is constructed from the skeleton of [[敎]]/[[教]] ("to teach") with the addition of two extra components: 1) a [[臼]]-like component around the top-left [[爻]] part, signifying hands (''[[hands-on]] teaching''); 2) a [[冖]] over [[子]] ("child"), representing the cover of a building or school, i.e. the child learns in a roofed place. ''{{w|Shuowen}}'' regards [[臼]] as the phonetic component in the character, which is unlikely to be true according to current Old Chinese reconstructions. Variant: [[斈]] ([[文]] "literature, writing" + 子 "child"). See [[敎]]/[[教]] for more.

